    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="1184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/30.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-04T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>313. Your 192. Please inform appropriate authorities that United States
                    Government can not submit to such an application of the provisions of the decree
                    of August 29 cancelling mining titles and declaring null all proceedings
                    relating to the acquirement of mining <pb facs="0843" n="727" xml:id="pg_727"/>
                    claims started during Huerta’s administration, as will result in the loss to
                    American citizens of rights or interests acquired in good faith and in
                    conformity with laws of Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
